description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Practice Experience Facilitator (Midwifery)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a registered and experienced midwife who is passionate about education? Do you enjoy motivating and enabling teams to drive improvements in the training and development of future healthcare professionals through learning? Do you want to work in a friendly, supportive and dynamic team? If the answer to this is yes, then we have an exciting challenge for you to join our Midwifery Education team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, innovative and motivated Band 7 to recruit into a ‘Practice Experience Facilitator (Midwifery)’ role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide an expert clinical role model working with matrons, ward managers and other key stakeholders to coordinate undergraduate practice learning experience within the Trust through the development of multi-professional education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will involve working with us to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the clinical placements at undergraduate and postgraduate levels across the nursing, midwifery and AHPs workforce.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate the learning and continuing professional development of the maternity workforce ensuring that education is responsive to service developments and also in line with the Trust Values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support the multi-professional workforce, including facilitation of career development opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Midwifery practice experience facilitator, you must be able to demonstrate a commitment to developing clinical placement provision across the different professional groups and show evidence of clinical leadership. You will work across multi-professional staff group to facilitate education, training and professional development through formal and informal teaching.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will involve providing teaching, training, competency assessment and support for a variety of leaners, including Student Midwives and RTP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An ability to develop and maintain excellent inter-professional partnership working with a range of stakeholders both internally and externally is essential for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note: This vacancy may close early once a sufficient amount of applications are received therefore early submission is advisory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
